<br>
Once the waves are all dealt with, untargetable high priest will be replaced by either lvl 60 high priest, or lvl 63 named priest and summon the char from the altar and try to pound him.   It's best that this char uses DA or DB at this point, and others take the priest down.  Either version of high priest has good chance of dropping lvl 60 Luclin spells (including KEI, Aegolism, etc) The whole ring lasts about 42 minutes, unless char on altar gets killed, then it resets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub47.ezboard.com/bblackburrowstoutco13800.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skorth>Skorth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/5/02 4:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub47.ezboard.com/fblackburrowstoutco13800frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=139.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mini ring.</span><hr size=1> If someone has already said this then fine, but anyway AoE groups rule here. k thx. =-)<br>
